commit 1c47da58766b93af0eb67d75985449b1fd1dd5ab
Author: DoubleGate <parobek@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun May 31 23:25:04 2026 -0400

    feat(v2.0): Phase 3 — gate the sprite shifter on rendering (Stale BG + Stale Sprite t3)
    
    Second increment of the ppu-sprite-shifter-counter cluster (default OFF). The
    sprite X-COUNTER decrements every visible dot regardless of rendering (already
    true — emit_pixel runs every visible dot 1..=256; AccuracyCoin "Stale Sprite
    Shift Regs" test 2), but the SHIFTER must PAUSE in forced blank so a sprite's
    pattern data is preserved across a long blank and still draws when rendering
    re-enables (test 3). RustyNES shifted unconditionally -> the data was shifted
    away during the blank -> no sprite-zero hit -> fail.
    
    emit_pixel (feature on): the spr_shift_lo/hi `<<= 1` is now gated on
    `mask_visible.rendering_enabled()` — the same 1-PPU-dot-delayed gate the BG
    shifter (shift_bg) uses; the counter decrement stays unconditional. Default
    (feature off): unconditional shift (byte-identical).
    
    Validation (feature on): "Stale BG Shift Registers" Fail -> PASS (bonus — its
    test 4 rides the sprite counter); "Stale Sprite Shift Regs" advances error 3 ->
    error 5 (test 3 — the shifter-pause — now passes; it now fails at test 5, the
    dot-339 "halted vs counting" counter-state reload, a future increment).
    AccuracyCoin (r4) 27 -> 26 fail; cpu_interrupts_v2 5/5; ppu_vbl_nmi 10/10;
    nes-ppu 41/41; Sprite 0 Hit + overflow still pass; clippy clean (default +
    feature); default build byte-identical.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

diff --git a/crates/nes-ppu/src/ppu.rs b/crates/nes-ppu/src/ppu.rs
index 24ae1a6..719a6fc 100644
--- a/crates/nes-ppu/src/ppu.rs
+++ b/crates/nes-ppu/src/ppu.rs
@@ -1694,12 +1694,28 @@ impl Ppu {
         self.framebuffer[off + 3] = rgba[3];
 
         // Decrement sprite X-counters / shift sprite shift regs.
+        //
+        // v2.0 Phase 3 (ppu-sprite-shifter-counter): the X-COUNTER decrements
+        // on every visible dot regardless of rendering (AccuracyCoin "Stale
+        // Sprite Shift Regs" test 2 — forced blank does NOT halt the
+        // counters), but the SHIFTER only advances while rendering is ENABLED
+        // (test 3 — the shifter PAUSES in forced blank, so a sprite's data is
+        // preserved across a long blank and still draws when rendering
+        // re-enables). `mask_visible.rendering_enabled()` is the same 1-PPU-dot
+        // delayed gate the BG shifter (`shift_bg`) uses. Default (feature off):
+        // the shifter advances unconditionally (legacy behaviour).
         for i in 0..self.spr_count as usize {
             if self.spr_x[i] > 0 {
                 self.spr_x[i] -= 1;
             } else {
-                self.spr_shift_lo[i] <<= 1;
-                self.spr_shift_hi[i] <<= 1;
+                #[cfg(feature = "ppu-sprite-shifter-counter")]
+                let do_shift = mask_v.rendering_enabled();
+                #[cfg(not(feature = "ppu-sprite-shifter-counter"))]
+                let do_shift = true;
+                if do_shift {
+                    self.spr_shift_lo[i] <<= 1;
+                    self.spr_shift_hi[i] <<= 1;
+                }
             }
         }
     }
